summary: [my gifs] // requester: @steverogershield // request here  “Guys!” you clapped your hands together excitedly, a wide grin on...
caption:
[my gifs] // requester: @steverogershield // request here

“Guys!” you clapped your hands together excitedly, a wide grin on your face. “I know what we should dress up as for Halloween!” 

Tony turned around, perplexed, as Clint’s gaze flickered up to meet yours. Waving your hands, you announced, “Disney princes and princesses!”

The room fell silent for a second as everyone looked amongst each other. It didn’t take long for a delighted smile to spread across Thor’s face as he boomed, “What a wonderful idea! Yes, I remember you insisting we watch those Disney movies together.”

Steve let out an amused chuckle. “That’s a sweet idea, y/n.”

“Eh, I don’t know.” Rhodey frowned, who wasn’t particularly excited about Halloween in general.

Too your surprise, Natasha rolled her eyes before looping an arm around your shoulder, encouraging, “Oh come on, it’s a fun idea. Let’s do it, y/n.”

summary:
I miss Bruce Banner, the one I know, before his personality was ripped out and switched for another.
The slow and careful way he...
body:
I miss Bruce Banner, the one I know, before his personality was ripped out and switched for another.

The slow and careful way he always talked, unless it was one of those rare cases where he was trying to manipulate the situation. And he was an expert at those.

All those little instances where you realize how witty and snarky and sassy he really was;

“How’s he doing?”

“Well, unfortunately he’s still Barton.”

“That’s terrible.”

The way he balks from authority at first, but how knowledgeable and commanding he really can be shows itself sometimes, peeking around the corner, after which he almost apologizes every time. For being himself.

The amazing tentative relationships he was finally starting to have with every single one of his teammates.

How he would never brag like Tony, usually tried to downplay what he did unless it was wrecking New York.

All the little tidbits that made up Bruce Banner, thrown out for a completely new one. In Thor: Ragnarok, in Avengers: Infinity War, and most likely Avengers 4, too.
